                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="16835" author="krondix" created="Wed, 15 Mar 2006 22:58:16 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Sorry, I&apos;ve found an earlier reported bug, &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.spring.io/browse/SPR-1783&quot; title=&quot;AspectJAutoproxyCreater does not honor usePrefix flag&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SPR-1783&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SPR-1783&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17184" author="adrian.colyer" created="Fri, 14 Apr 2006 02:21:50 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This issue is resolved in 2.0 M4.  The AspectJAutoProxyCreator was asking the AjTypeSystem if a given type was an aspect, but not differentiating between @AspectJ aspects and code style aspects. The first part of the fix is to not try and auto-proxy using a code-style AspectJ aspect. This is sufficient to enable &amp;lt;aop:spring-configured&amp;gt; and &amp;lt;aop:aspectj-autoproxy&amp;gt; to be used in conjunction. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;There remains the issue that you might want to DI some @AspectJ aspects woven with AspectJ into e.g. the domain model, and still autoproxy with some other @AspectJ aspects in e.g. the service layer with Spring AOP. Right now there is no way to exclude the domain aspects from inclusion in the autoproxying process. I&apos;m going to raise a separate enhancement request to cover this.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
